title: For Sale:  RARE All Original WW2 1944 Colt 1911A1 With Extra Scoville Magazine
postcontent:
Don't miss out on this hard to find piece of history! I have a Colt 1911A1 .45 ACP, serial number 1694XXX manufactured in 1944. It likely saw combat in WWII based on the light wear and patina, but despite that, survived the war completely intact. As far as I can tell, it is completely original and collector grade. Original finish, "Colt .45" barrel, grips, trigger, everything. The magazine, which has the correct C-S (Colt-Scoville) stamp, is a contracted magazine that late-WWII 1911A1s were shipped with. Internal parts are all factory original and in very good condition. Appropriate roll marks and proof marks are all present and strong.

I also have a Scoville "S" magazine that will be included. The Scoville magazines were not shipped with Colt 1911A1s, but were produced and shipped during WWII. It comes with a reproduction Kraft box that does have matching serial number and looks pretty cool as a display piece. 

Completely factory original Colt 1911A1s are becoming much more difficult to find. This pistol has been meticulously maintained and will make a great addition to any Colt collection! Sorry, but I'm not looking to trade anything for the pistol. Don't hesitate to e-mail with any questions!

One is the Smith & Wesson M&P 15-22 rifle and the other is the Walther P22 pistol. Both are wildly popular .22LR platforms that deliver AR and CQC style form factors in the .22LR caliber that allows reasonable shooting costs coupled with the look, feel, and handling of their popular larger caliber cousins.
